::With that, she turned away and retreated back into the forest, no longer interested to dwell on this matter. She did not trust the girl. Perhaps she never would, but Dawn was being stubborn as always and it wasn't fair to Belle, not matter what the feeling she gave off. Sartha would judge her in her own way...:: <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fbe5b4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/udawnithinia.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Dawnithinia </A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_fire.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Amazon Queen</span><br>  Posts: 98<br> <font color=#993300>(5/26/01 5:10:56 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=134.topic&index=34>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=AmazonWarMaskofDeath WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Yes mam</span><hr size=1>  Dawn gripped the reigns of the horse, and nickered. The horse turned and retreated onto the trail leading back to Orio-Pata.<br>
 <br>
 Maybe she was being stubborn but it was Dawn they were talking about. You could never tell how she would treat anyone, and since her episode with Keecho and Cupid things had come alot easier for her. Keecho was still in her life, but she had allowed someone she thought she could never rely on, to kill Cupid. Now he was dead, and Keecho was just a platonic relationship.<br>
 <br>
 Dawn was once again back to her old ways. If Belle prooved to be what Dawn could respect her attitude would change toward her, and if Belle didn't give her a warm welcome then she didn't deserve the respect. Dawn was an old immortal creature. The predator is always cautious. This assassin had learned that through the years. Belle was being given her chance, Sartha just didn't know it. Her message had been sent from the mind. Not even Alysia knew it. <p>Pyschotic injustice
