Belle sighed softly as she saw Dawn ride off... She'd found it difficult to pay attention, even to her own coronation, when there was so much distrust in the crowd... She'd watched Sartha and Dawn argue in the distance, and knew it was Dawn's voice which popped into her head... It was going to be a long road, indeed.<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fbe5b4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/ualysiaofscynthia.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Alysia of Scynthia</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>registered user</span><br>  Posts: 98<br> <font color=#993300>(5/28/01 10:30:20 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=134.topic&index=36>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Coronation of Princess Belle</span><hr size=1> Alysia sighed as she watched Dawn ride off. She knew that no one gained Dawn's respect without earning it. Not even Aly had that sorta luck. She knew Dawn was a great asset to the Amazon Nation. Anyone who possed a threat to the sisters, had to deal with Dawn. . . as much as Aly valued her strengths in the tribe, she too felt that Dawn's mistrusting others could indeed be a weakness as well.<br>
<br>
Alysia sighed and watched again as her athelfi left the coronation of her daughter. It had been a long time since Dawn and Aly had been close. They were good friends long ago. But something had changed. Changed them both.<br>
<br>
Wulf.<br>
<br>
<br>
Alysia held back her tears as she thought about her son. Not a day passed by that Aly didn't think of him. But now was not the time for tears, it was Belle's day. And nothing would change that.<br>
<br>
Alysia smiled as she reached into a small bowl of water. She looked at it as some of the drops fall back against her skin. She remembered long ago when it was custom to bathe the new sisters in blood. But that was no longer a need. At least not for this ceremony. She pushed Belle's head forward and let the water pour over her daughter's head.<br>
<br>
&quot;A queen is a chalice. Let us fill you with visions of our history, fragments of a time before we were Amazons,<br>
when cannibals slaughtered our men, and warriors like the great Samsara called on the shaman for a savior from the future, an Atmah . . . the first Cyane.&quot;<br>
<br>
She then reached into a small pouch and pulled out some petals of a daisy, she then set them into Belle's hand and began humming that same little song that Vyiana always did. Vyiana was the Atmah Cyane, in one life at least. Belle should remember and be honored to have her as a sister.<br>
<br>
&quot;Tonight your coronation continues a ritual passed<br>
down to us through the ages. A ritual of music and movement, a celebration of community and joy, for we are a family, united in sisterhood.  We are the creators and our own creations, The words and the music, both singer and song.  Our traditions stretch back to the great Gaea herself, mother of us all, a tradition of dance-- of music-- of sacrifice-- of blood.&quot;<br>
<br>
She then reached over and grabbed a small chalice that held the best Scynthian wine found. Alysia handed it to Belle and smiled.<br>
<br>
&quot;This wine symbolizes the blood we used to use. The blood of our sisters that have fallen before us. Drink it as a symbol of your honor and loyalty to your sisters. To yout tribe.&quot;  <br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
